President Cyril Ramaphosa will be updating the nation on the developments in the fight against coronavirus at 7:30pm. This amid fears of a COVID-19 resurgence after the Easter holidays. Some quarters have called for stricter restrictions this Easter in bid to avoid a third wave. This as the country continues to see a steady rise in the number of coronavirus cases. South Africa currently has 1 545 979 coronavirus cases and 52 710 deaths. Live proceedings in the stream below: 